et purchase at crater rim\",\n753\t          \"body\": \"A Maasai lady at the Ngorongoro crater rim sold two beaded bracelets for Athina Mari. Paid approximately TZS 35,000 (~$20-25 USD).\",\n754\t          \"category\": \"voice_memo\",\n755\t          \"trip_part\": \"safari\",\n756\t          \"related_contact\": \"\"\n757\t        },\n758\t        {\n759\t          \"id\": \"241fb553-a6c4-4941-bf29-900deeecdca1\",\n760\t          \"title\": \"Extra ranger tip at Ngorongoro gate\",\n761\t          \"body\": \"Emmanuel warned of an extra ranger tip of ~TZS 5,000 cash at the gate, separate from park fees. Vasileios wants to confirm this with Richard before the safari balance payment.\",\n762\t          \"category\": \"voice_memo\",\n763\t          \"trip_part\": \"safari\",\n764\t          \"related_contact\": \"Richard (Suricata Safaris)\"\n765\t        },\n766\t        {\n767\t          \"id\": \"603a15be-f103-465c-afe6-d7d0178b93a8\",\n768\t          \"title\": \"Crater day - best day of my life\",\n769\t          \"body\": \"The Ngorongoro Crater day was described as \\\"one of the best days of my life.\\\"\",\n770\t          \"category\": \"voice_memo\",\n771\t          \"trip_part\": \"safari\",\n772\t          \"related_contact\": \"\"\n773\t        },\n774\t        {\n775\t          \"id\": \"7e0f1146-face-4474-a54c-c513b0976f44\",\n776\t          \"title\": \"Stone Town courtyard photo note\",\n777\t          \"body\": \"A bright courtyard with white stucco walls, arched windows, and ornate dark balconies under a clear blue sky.\",\n778\t          \"category\": \"photo_note\",\n779\t          \"trip_part\": \"zanzibar\",\n780\t          \"related_contact\": \"\"\n781\t        },\n782\t        {\n783\t          \"id\": \"1d816bf3-006e-429a-8252-328ec7edf87e\",\n784\t          \"title\": \"Safari balance payment - confirm with Richard\",\n785\t          \"body\": \"Balance $960 due on arrival in Arusha. Cash preferred (USD, post-2009 notes). Pesapal online adds 5% surcharge. Vasileios should confirm the ranger tip situation with Richard before paying.\",\n786\t          \"category\": \"todo\",\n787\t          \"trip_part\": \"arusha\",\n788\t          \"related_contact\": \"Richard (Suricata Safaris)\"\n789\t        },\n790\t        {\n791\t          \"id\": \"c68b6f34-402d-4dc4-b1e5-4215e4ba67f9\",\n792\t          \"title\": \"Ngorongoro nights are cold\",\n793\t          \"body\": \"Warm layers needed for Ngorongoro Crater nights. August is cool at elevation.\",\n794\t          \"category\": \"key_learning\",\n795\t          \"trip_part\": \"safari\",\n796\t          \"related_contact\": \"\"\n797\t        },\n798\t        {\n799\t          \"id\": \"2febf742-9fcb-4f59-a5d6-02a565364698\",\n800\t          \"title\": \"Zanzibar swimming - north coast best\",\n801\t          \"body\": \"For Zanzibar swimming: north coast (Nungwi area) offers more consistent conditions vs. east/south coasts where low tide limits access.\",\n802\t          \"category\": \"tip\",\n803\t          \"trip_part\": \"zanzibar\",\n804\t          \"related_contact\": \"\"\n805\t        },\n806\t        {\n807\t          \"id\": \"4e22c6de-770c-4882-b640-0f3eb50320d1\",\n808\t          \"title\": \"Tanzania e-visa mandatory online\",\n809\t          \"body\": \"Tanzania e-visa is mandatory online ($50/person) at visa.immigration.go.tz; visa-on-arrival no longer available as of January 2025. Zanzibar also requires separate mandatory travel insurance from ZIC.\",\n810\t          \"category\": \"key_learning\",\n811\t          \"trip_part\": \"general\",\n812\t          \"related_contact\": \"\"\n813\t        },\n814\t        {\n815\t          \"id\": \"570fef74-cab4-4ef0-b66d-ee0ab007e29a\",\n816\t          \"title\": \"Egypt e-visa multiple-entry\",\n817\t          \"body\": \"Egypt e-visa is multiple-entry ($65); both travelers apply separately. Egyptian e-visa requires a mandatory printed copy.\",\n818\t          \"category\": \"key_learning\",\n819\t          \"trip_part\": \"cairo\",\n820\t          \"related_contact\": \"\"\n821\t        },\n822\t        {\n823\t          \"id\": \"e98eab5b-f02f-42b8-b634-d510420cc4bc\",\n824\t          \"title\": \"Precision Air luggage restrictions\",\n825\t          \"body\": \"Precision Air flights (TC144/TC145) have luggage restrictions favoring soft bags.\",\n826\t          \"category\": \"tip\",\n827\t          \"trip_part\": \"general\",\n828\t          \"related_contact\": \"\"\n829\t        },\n830\t        {\n831\t          \"id\": \"09986e1c-a857-4c2c-a81b-fca7fc2fc8f5\",\n832\t          \"title\": \"August is peak safari season\",\n833\t          \"body\": \"August is peak safari season — ideal for wildlife, including the Great Wildebeest Migration corridor.\",\n834\t          \"category\": \"observation\",\n835\t          \"trip_part\": \"safari\",\n836\t          \"related_contact\": \"\"\n837\t        },\n838\t        {\n839\t          \"id\": \"07babe3d-308a-42b0-a976-442cb253909a\",\n840\t          \"title\": \"Zanzibar driving permit required\",\n841\t          \"body\": \"Vasilis holds an International Driving Permit (IDP). A local Zanzibar Driving Permit is also required (~$15, valid up to 3 months). Most rental companies arrange this with a license photo provided 24+ hours before arrival. Police checkpoints are frequent; carry both IDP and local permit (screenshot acceptable).\",\n842\t          \"category\": \"tip\",\n843\t          \"trip_part\": \"zanzibar\",\n844\t          \"related_contact\": \"\"\n845\t        },\n846\t        {\n847\t          \"id\": \"3ec610e2-92fe-4c0c-9888-28cce236ae74\",\n848\t          \"title\": \"Cairo Stopover 1 sightseeing\",\n849\t          \"body\": \"Grand Egyptian Museum and Pyramids of Giza (Aug 3-4). Eileen Hotel is near Tahrir Square/Nile Corniche.\",\n850\t          \"category\": \"observation\",\n851\t          \"trip_part\": \"cairo\",\n852\t          \"related_contact\": \"\"\n853\t        },\n854\t        {\n855\t          \"id\": \"a3f4b401-fa28-4d6b-a5c8-19a2f1d47de9\",\n856\t          \"title\": \"Cairo Stopover 2 sightseeing\",\n857\t          \"body\": \"Islamic Cairo, the Citadel, Khan el-Khalili bazaar, Coptic Cairo (Aug 19-20). Ramses Hilton is the base; taxi needed between Citadel and Coptic Cairo.\",\n858\t          \"category\": \"observation\",\n859\t          \"trip_part\": \"cairo\",\n860\t          \"related_contact\": \"\"\n861\t        },\n862\t        {\n863\t          \"id\": \"faefd84c-604e-43ba-b315-93b242f005f8\",\n864\t          \"title\": \"Dar es Salaam exploration ideas\",\n865\t          \"body\": \"Arriving by ferry from Zanzibar; interest in city exploration: Kivukoni Fish Market, Kariakoo Market, National Museum, Coco Beach, Bongoyo Island.\",\n866\t          \"category\": \"observation\",\n867\t          \"trip_part\": \"dar\",\n868\t          \"related_contact\": \"\"\n869\t        }\n870\t      ]\n871\t    },\n872\t    \"appManifest\": {\n873\t      \"tables\": [\n874\t        {\n875\t          \"name\": \"contacts\",\n876\t          \"schema\": {\n877\t            \"title\": \"Contacts & People\",\n878\t            \"description\": \"All contacts, service providers, and people involved in the trip.\",\n879\t            \"columns\": {\n880\t              \"id\": {\n881\t                \"type\": \"string\",\n882\t                \"description\": \"Primary key\",\n883\t                \"primaryKey\": true,\n884\t                \"generated\": \"uuid\"\n885\t              },\n886\t              \"name\": {\n887\t                \"type\": \"string\",\n888\t                \"description\": \"Name of person or business\"\n889\t              },\n890\t              \"role\": {\n891\t                \"type\": \"string\",\n892\t                \"description\": \"Role: safari, lodging, dining, transport, insurance, guide, other\"\n893\t              },\n894\t              \"phone\": {\n895\t                \"type\": \"string\",\n896\t       