{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_8wVYcO5LlRnvetURl3DZK8MH","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# scenario-campaign instance\n2\t\n3\tRuns each scenario in `sdk/org/scenarios/<id>/` — now a single declarative **`scenario.yaml`**\n4\t(persona · promise · invariants · steps) plus **`fixtures/`** — end-to-end against a LOCAL\n5\t`lmthing serve`, **judges every step** on the execution trace + real state, and on the FIRST failure\n6\t**fixes it at the right rung** (L0 scenario / L1 prompt / L2 structure / L3 framework) and **proves\n7\tthe fix with a fresh rerun**. One failure per invocation; if a scenario is fully green, the judge\n8\tauthors ONE extension and stops. There is **no per-scenario `run.mjs` and no `results/` dir** — a\n9\tgeneric YAML runner plays the steps, and the judge's report lives beside its progress log in the\n10\tround-artifact tree.\n11\t\n12\t## The prompts\n13\t\n14\t| File | Role |\n15\t|---|---|\n16\t| `scenario-spec.md` | shared foundation: the `scenario.yaml` format, the four real-person rules, the three-store contract, the invariant library (incl. \"Asking well\"), the feature map, generalize-never-overfit. `{{include}}`d by the three below. |\n17\t| `judge.md` | the round template — run → judge → answer THING's questions in-persona → on first failure fix at the right rung → verify with a fresh rerun → stop; extend if fully green. **Never commits.** |\n18\t| `create.md` | manual entrypoint: author a brand-new `scenario.yaml` + real fixtures. |\n19\t| `extend.md` | grow an existing green scenario in-persona toward an untouched capability. |\n20\t| `prompt.continue.md` | cross-account resume wrapper that honors never-commit. |\n21\t\n22\t## The human is the commit gate\n23\t\n24\tThe judge **never commits** — it leaves its changes uncommitted with a full report (the interface to\n25\treview). **A human reviews the diff against the report and commits directly to `main`.** So this\n26\tinstance runs **serially** (`maxParallel: 1`) and is meant to be driven **one scenario at a time**:\n27\t\n28\t```bash\n29\tnode automation/lmauto.mjs run scenario-campaign --dry-run    # preview the next run's prompt\n30\tnode automation/lmauto.mjs run scenario-campaign              # ONE run, returns (next in rotation)\n31\tnode automation/lmauto.mjs run scenario-campaign 06-tanzania  # force a specific scenario\n32\tnode automation/lmauto.mjs tui scenario-campaign              # dashboard"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_cwYgt85iKLtg0vqZsWTtUM66","session_id":"b8a0991b-bce4-420b-844a-664f990ff54b","uuid":"91c61e38-e7f7-438e-91fa-ae9135da4a04","timestamp":"2026-07-15T22:47:40.383Z","subagent_type":"Explore","task_description":"Trace specialist creation route"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_XEauNDMoaGNmnZbbEgDnXNih","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tinput:\n3\t  query: string\n4\t---\n5\t\n6\tAnswer a question that spans more than one place — some parts are about TOPICS owned by specialist\n7\tspaces, some are about the USER's own data in the DB/memory. Step one splits the question into\n8\tself-contained sub-questions, each tagged with who should answer it; step two asks each owning space\n9\tin parallel; step three gathers the user's own parts (DB + memory) and reasons over everything into\n10\tone answer. The goal output is `{ answer, sources }`.\n11\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_cwYgt85iKLtg0vqZsWTtUM66","session_id":"b8a0991b-bce4-420b-844a-664f990ff54b","uuid":"4ed43dbb-97b9-46b0-a658-31664126434d","timestamp":"2026-07-15T22:47:40.384Z","subagent_type":"Explore","task_description":"Trace specialist creation route"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_J4Gb5a2y8WinhujRVHM8NgIL","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tinput:\n3\t  claim: string\n4\t  existing: object\n5\t---\n6\t\n7\tTwo sources disagree about the same fact and we must decide which stands. `claim` is the new/asserted\n8\tvalue (with, ideally, where it came from); `existing` describes what is already stored and where.\n9\tStep one gathers the competing values and each one's PROVENANCE; step two applies the precedence\n10\t**user-asserted > DB > researched > guess** — and when two EQUALLY authoritative sources collide, it\n11\tdoes not pick silently, it returns a decision to ask the user. The goal output is `{ decision, winner,\n12\tdetail }` where `decision` ∈ `keep` | `replace` | `ask`.\n13\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_cwYgt85iKLtg0vqZsWTtUM66","session_id":"b8a0991b-bce4-420b-844a-664f990ff54b","uuid":"2beca4ad-f3c1-469c-84b7-d386eea75a91","timestamp":"2026-07-15T22:47:40.385Z","subagent_type":"Explore","task_description":"Trace specialist creation route"}
