{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"msg_36c8defa-ddc8-4f50-9e6d-44a73b5aa603","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"call_TRXLoC5poHgSdtkGI5fTx8iN","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md","old_string":"   **When the material splits into distinct PARTS, build the spaces too — they will never ask for\nthem.** Substantial material usually has natural parts (per place, per stage, per client, per\npiece of equipment). Before delegating, make a COMPLETE inventory of the independently owned\nscopes in the supplied material. Create one specialist for every scope with its own facts; do not\nreplace any of them with a generic catch-all. A part having only a few facts is NOT a reason to\nfold it into a broader one — a small distinct part still gets its own specialist; brevity is not a\nmerge. A broad overview or cross-cutting aggregate can supplement the scope specialists only for\nfacts that belong to no particular scope; it never replaces them. Give each part its own specialist\nspace, grounded in the provided content (path 3's ALREADY-PROVIDED shortcut — the\narchitect, no re-research), so a later plain question about that part is answered from real\nknowledge instead of a stale summary. This is YOUR judgment call, not a request to relay: the\nuser does not know what a specialist is and must never be asked to name one. Build the parts\nfirst, then the app, and report both in the terms they used — the parts of their own material,\nnever the machinery.\n","new_string":"   **When the material splits into distinct PARTS, build the spaces too — they will never ask for\nthem.** Substantial material usually has natural parts (per place, per stage, per client, per\npiece of equipment). A stable part with its own facts gets one specialist; an individual expense,\nnote, reminder, or fact stays in the app data rather than becoming a specialist. A broad overview\nor cross-cutting aggregate can supplement the scope specialists only for facts that belong to no\nparticular scope; it never replaces them. This is YOUR judgment call, not a request to relay: the\nuser does not know what a specialist is and must never be asked to name one. Build the parts first,\nthen the app, and report both in the terms they used — the parts of their own material, never the\nmachinery.\n"}}],"model":"gpt-5.6-terra","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b8a0991b-bce4-420b-844a-664f990ff54b","uuid":"d1f8fef5-3f1f-40d5-bb86-a2a13372074a"}
